Results.ReviewText: I have drank Nescafe original for over 10 years, it has always been my favourite, nothing beats it, there was no other coffee I would drink.  However..... Nescafe have just changed their faultless coffee to be 'double filtered' with the new red lid and it is absolutely disgusting! I cannot drink it! Never one to waste money but actually had to throw a jar away because no one wanted it! Awful move of Nescafe! In my social circle alone I know of four or five families who are now switching brands.  Sorry Nescafe.... you've lost me as a customer certainly and I'm sure there will be a few to follow!  Bring back your decent Nescafe original!
Results.Title: No longer original and certainly not the best!

ClientResponses.Response:
We're really sorry to hear about your disappointment with the recent changes we've made to our Nescafé Original.

We worked on trying to make it a more enjoyable cup for you by developing some tech that in two steps helps to maintain the full flavour and aroma of our Nescafé Original, whilst taking out harsher and bitter compounds (Double Filter).

Results.ReviewText: Like other reviewers I have just bought a red top jar of Nescafe Original as I couldnt find the brown top one in the shop.  I also assumed that it was just a new jar colour.  Wrong!  When I got home and compared the red one with my old brown jar, I saw that the brown top one is described as "Classic" whereas the red top is "Original".  Well, it might have been an 'origina'l recipe at one point, but there is no way it tastes anything like the Classic one I have enjoyed for over 30 years.  Not impressed, Nescafe, I feel that I have been conned!  This red top stuff tastes like it contains chicory.. won't be buying it again.
Results.Title: Tastes of chicory now

ClientResponses.Response: Hi, we’ve worked on trying to make this a more enjoyable cup for you by developing some tech that in two steps helps to maintain the full flavour and aroma of our Nescafé Original, whilst taking out harsher and bitter compounds (Double Filter). We’re really sorry you’re not a fan of the changes but thank you very much for letting us know.

Results.ReviewText: What has happened to my favourite drink.  Since Nescafe Original went Red Top it tastes beyond awful.  It has completely lost it's rich, full bodied coffee flavour and become tasteless & bitter with a burnt smell and taste. The double filtering has filtered out all the good stuff and left us with something that, to my pallet (& I love a good coffee) is now undrinkable.  I had hoped that my 1st Jar was just a bad batch but having tasted a second jar I have today returned it to the place of purchase and got my money back. I've been drinking it for 50 years but I'll not be buying it ever again.   Unfortunalty it wouldn't let me give a rating of less than 1 star. Please Please bring back the Brown Top
Results.Title: The most awful coffee I've ever tasted

ClientResponses.Response: Hi, we’re always looking for ways to improve your experience with our coffee and that’s why we decided to try & make this a more enjoyable cup for you! We’re really sorry to hear how much you didn’t enjoy our new Nescafé Original but really appreciate your feedback. We’ve made a note of all your comments & will be passing them on to the rest of the team.

Results.ReviewText: The covert introduction of a new product to replace a well loved and rightly popular flavour told us all we needed to know really - namely that you weren't confident of the new flavour either.  You can hide behind the 'Oh, of course people will complain whenever change occurs' card as much as you like, but you won't stop the unprecedented dislike of your replacement original flavour.  You could of course let the customers do the talking, by once again making the original flavour available, but I suspect  acknowledging you have made a mistake in public will be a step too far.
Results.Title: How to alienate your clients

ClientResponses.Response:
Hi, Nescafé Original is the brand name, rather than it being Original Nescafé. This is simply an improved formula for this blend & it has been done on several occasions over the last 77+ years.

We’ve worked on trying to make this a more enjoyable cup for you by developing some tech that in two steps helps to maintain the full flavour and aroma of our Nescafé Original, whilst taking out harsher and bitter compounds (Double Filter).

All jars that were produced before we made these changes sold through before our 'New & Improved' jars became available so they won't be available to purchase now, sorry.

We’re also really sorry to hear you’re disappointed with the changes but we’ll let the rest of the team know.

Results.ReviewText:
If you improve a coffee it is not original. I have been drinking Nescafé original since the late 50s when it was sold in tins and was a power.
A natural choice because my grandfather worked for nestles in Aylesbury for 52 years and bought starff sales. Last week I bought the New improved "original" poured half of a 300gram jar into a coffee container and sniffed.
No smell of coffee just a mild nondescript not very pleasant smell.
What have you done to my coffee to detract any aroma and taste from it.
I thought it was me getting old until my wife tried it and accused me of buying some cheap brown granules from somewhere.
Can you please tell me where can I buy some original NOT improved Nescafé that actually tastes like it comes from coffee beans?
Results.Title: New and improved original

Results.ReviewText: I have been drinking strong black coffee for nearly 40 years. I look forward to my Nescafe Original kick-start in the morning.  I have had other coffee's but never liked the taste. I do not like filter coffee and never buy it from coffee houses or cafe's when I am out. The burnt aftertaste totally puts me off. I take my Nescafe with me everywhere even on holiday. I am very disappointed with the new product it leaves a nasty taste in your mouth. Why change it? I wont be buying Nescafe again its dreadful.
Results.Title: Very Disappointed Why change the perfect coffee

ClientResponses.Response:
Hi,

Here at Nescafé we’re always looking for ways to improve your experience so we developed some tech that in two steps helps to maintain the full flavour and aroma of our Nescafé Original, whilst taking out harsher and bitter compounds (Double Filter). This results in making it even more of an enjoyable cup for you!

We’re really sorry to hear how much you didn’t enjoy our new Nescafé Original but really appreciate your feedback.

We’ve made a note of all your comments & will be passing them on to the appropriate department.
ClientResponses.Name: Natalie Farmeary

Results.ReviewText: Got this jar as there was not one with a brown lid in the shop, just thought it was a new jar design and didn't realise until I tasted it that the contents had changed also.  Luckily I managed to track down a normal jar as I did not like the flavour at all and will not be drinking it.  I have drank Nescafe Original for the best part of my coffee drinking life and now I am desperate to find another coffee as that is pretty much all I drink, about 10 cups a day.  Why change something that worked and after looking at all of the latest reviews I am obviously not the only one who thinks that way as all are negative.  Are you going to bring the other one back?  Please do, but in the mean time I have no alternative to change brands and hope to find a decent coffee.  If any old original drinkers have found a good alternative please share with me, thanks
Results.Title: New Original?  Please bring the other back

Results.ReviewText:
Why change something that is already perfect, the only answer must be cost saving.
While the new version isn't awful it certainly is not an improvement in either taste or aroma.
I have always drunk Nescafe Original and for the last few years I have drunk it black so I notice the difference even more than someone who has milk. I have always tried to be the first one to break the seal on a new jar because I just loved that burst of aroma that comes with it, now that has been ruined it's just not the same any more.
Results.Title: Not an improvement

Results.ReviewText:
Sorry to tell you but your change to Nescafé Original makes it no longer original. It seems to have lost all it's flavour. It might fit American taste but we in the UK like a stronger flavour. Hopefully, like Coca-Cola when they altered 'coke' and found consumers didn't like it, you will go back to the 'Original'.  I might point out also that 'New improved original' is an oxymoron too.
For the moment - I'll be looking for another brand.
Results.Title: You made a big mistake!

Results.ReviewText: Only drink Nescafe and all my friends know to have it in if I am visiting cannot drink any other coffee and can only drink out of nescafe cups lucky was down to last cup from years ago when you started giving them again yipee
Results.Title: Only one coffee Nescafe

ClientResponses.Response:
Hi Danny

Thank you very much for taking the time to let us know your thoughts.

Here at Nescafé we’re always looking for ways to improve your coffee experience, so we developed this new recipe, which maintains the bold, full flavour that consumers love, but reduces some of the more bitter flavours that could also be found in the old recipe.  The feedback we received in consumer research was that this results in making Nescafé Original a more enjoyable cup of coffee.

Any changes to our products are the result of rigorous research and development as we believe in producing products with a great taste, consistent levels of quality and safety, value for money and convenience.

We always value feedback from our consumers and this is particularly important when loyal consumers comment on any changes we have made. We were sorry to hear of your disappointment with the recent changes we’ve made to Nescafé Original and we will pass your comments to the brand team who take on board all the feedback they receive for future product development.

Thank you once again for taking the trouble to contact us. We hope that in future you will enjoy our products.

Kind regards

Tom - NESCAFÉ Team

Results.ReviewText: I have tasted other coffees, both cheaper and more expensive, but I always returned to Nescafe for decades. It disappeared from my main online supplier then returned to it but more expensive.So, I eventually bought several jars from another one. I wondered what had happened to the taste. I now see it is "New Improved". Well it is half as strong as before and tastes nothing like the original. I might as well buy a cheaper coffee, different brand. I am very annoyed you have changed the coffee to taste just the same as weaker so called "smoother" coffees. They in fact now taste better than Nescafe.
Results.Title: Will not buy again

ClientResponses.Response: Thanks for your sharing your thoughts with us. We've made a note of your comments and passed them forward to the Brand Team who will be reviewing your feedback.

Results.ReviewText: My husband has been drinking Nescafe Original for probably 40 years, give or take a year or two but no longer.  He says the 'new improved' version is, and I quote, "revolting and tastes like decaffeinated".  He had not seen the new jar with the red lid (I had emptied it into our own container) so other than the taste he had no idea that the old brown lidded version had changed until he drank his first cup.  Off now to probably spend a small fortune trying to find a replacement that matches up to the original Original
Results.Title: Change for the worst!

ClientResponses.Response: Here at Nescafé we’re always looking for ways to improve your experience so we developed some tech that in two steps helps to maintain the full flavour and aroma of our Nescafé Original, whilst taking out harsher and bitter compounds (Double Filter). This results in making it more of an enjoyable cup for you! We're sorry to hear you're not happy with these changes but we'll be letting the rest of the team know.

Results.ReviewText: I have just opened a jar of "new improved" Nescafe Original and the once-special smell made me gag.  The coffee tastes bitter and strange - I know it it Christmas but I don't expect coffee to smell and taste like sprouts.  I wondered if it was just me but thankfully the internet is awash with complaints which is kind of reassuring.  I just hope they take note and change the receipe back.
Results.Title: I have always drunk Nescafe but...

Results.ReviewText: Calling the product 'original' when is made with a new process is clearly in error. The product no longer tastes like the previous brown lid version.  In fact to sell the product shops are marketing it at reduced price and do not appear to be re-stocking the previous version. I won't be buying it again and threw out my last purchase as did not like the new taste.
Results.Title: Changed product no longer tastes as good.

Results.ReviewText: I have been using the NESCAFÉ brand for many years, and although new flavours have been introduced, I always tend to veer back to the original. It's so full of flavour, whether made with water or milk, that I don't need to stock up on any other brands. I do tend to keep several of the sachet flavours at home (cappuccino,latte, creme caramel etc), mainly for visitors, but the sheer simplicity of making this fine tasting coffee means I don't use them that often. Although, I do admit to taking on a gold blend every now and again.  NESCAFÉ original has a great taste, it's a full flavour ground coffee and it doesn't fail to deliver on taste.
Results.Title: A faultless flavour

Results.ReviewText: Have been drinking Nescafe original for years. How can you say it is improved. From the moment you open the jar the aroma which you got from the original is missing. The taste  has gone it is on par with Baldricks coffee from Blackadder when Captain Blackadder asks what have we been drinking for the last 12 months the reply is mud.
Results.Title: New improved who you trying to fool

Results.ReviewText: Why have you changed it, I have been drinking nescafe original for longer than I care to remember I buy a 300g jar per week. I had to buy the jars with red lids last week as that was all that was available, I am very disappointed with the changes to the taste, so will have to start trying different brands
Results.Title: Why

Results.ReviewText: I have been buying Nescafé Original for as long as I can remember...I have tried others when money was tight but some things just have to be! For me it is my morning coffee and only Nescafé Original. It wakes up all my senses...the aroma, the reassuringly pleasant taste, the velvety sensation as I stir it through hot water in my mug, that little bit of steam rising off the top is a welcome sight every day and the way it makes me sigh after the first sip. I may be missing out on other Nescafé coffees...perhaps...but I won't change and cannot be tempted when the original in my opinion is already as good as it gets! Pop the kettle on....
Results.Title: Nostalgia Rules My Mornings!

ClientResponses.Response: Hi, we're really sorry to hear you're not a fan of the changes we've made recently but thank you for letting us know. We'll let the rest of the team know as well.

Results.ReviewText:
Myself and several of my friends and family have stopped buying Nescafe Original with the Red Top as the flavour is far from an improvement. I have scoured the shops to buy any remaining Brown Tops, but once these are used, I will have to switch brands, having drunk Nescafe Original for more years than I care to remember!
PLEASE BRING BACK THE BROWN TOP!
Results.Title: Bring Back the Brown Top!

Results.ReviewText:
I bought this as the original brown one was no longer available.
I have purchased 2 jars now, and still cannot get the flavour I used to have before.
The new double filter is too bitter however I make it.  I will be forced to switch to another brand.
Please bring back the old one!
Results.Title: Not for me

Results.ReviewText: After years of drinking Nescafe original, I will no longer be buying it since their "new and improved" recipe.  I agree totally with RedLidNotForMe, it's disgusting. Will be looking for an alternative that doesn't taste cheap.
Results.Title: disgusting

Results.ReviewText:
I think that with the number of negative reviews Nescafe really need to seriously consider bringing back the Original Brown Top, I asked my Son and Daughter in Law at the weekend (without bias) what they thought of the new Double filter Nescafe and they said "Awful!". I have now changed brands and I will not be purchasing the new inferior double filter ever again. I feel that a more constructive feedback from Nescafe istead of the generic one below would be appreciated!

Results.Title: Bring back the ORIGINAL ORIGINAL!

Results.ReviewText:
I hadn't brought Nescafe Original for a while as drank other brands, brought a jar liked the packaging a lot smarter.  I like the aroma which is really pleasant and rich and made me smile and also the taste is very smooth.

Value for money - you do pay a bit more than the other brands but you do get high quality coffee.  I did buy my coffee when it was on offer but would be happy to continue buying Nescafe at the rrp price.

I would rinse my mug/cup with boiling water to warm up, add coffee and then pour water that has just come of the boil. To me it seems to taste better than when you pour boiling water straight away (just tastes different).
Results.Title: Smarter Nescafe

We'll have to find another Brand with a similar flavour.
Results.Title: Newer does NOT mean better!

Results.ReviewText: This is watery and had lost the bitter coffee tast of the original and is more like goldblend. Why?
Results.Title: Being back the old one

Results.ReviewText:
As a drinker of the original Original I can say that this new double filter version is a poor imitation - the old adage applies ' if it ain't broke, don't fix it' 
The taste for me is unpalatable
Thanks for the memories
Goodbye Nescafe
Results.Title: Nescafe Original

Results.ReviewText: Have just purchased a new jar (been drinking classic Nescafe for about 30 plus years.  It doesn't taste the same as before.  Perhaps another example of changing something for the sake of it.  It does smell the same but I'm not convinced and a bit disappointed. Also I really do not like the red lid. It is very cheap looking - brown was much better - only my opinion though.
Results.Title: Have you changed the taste?

Results.ReviewText: I have to agree with other reviews regarding new Nescafe. Please bring back old one I have tried to get used to new flavour but honestly don't like it , I will have to change brands after drinking Nescafe for many years.
Results.Title: Bring back old Nescafe
